reviews_data.review_text: The bang for your buck here goes a long way
To call the food subpar would be generous. The majority of workers were friendly enough but not enough for me to ignore the participation in gentrification that the owner has conducted.
One of a kind cafe housed in an old service station.  Home made eats, including roasting their coffee in house.  Burgers & sandwiches, fantastic breakfast grub.  Beer & wine available.

What a gem!  The best biscuits we ever had. Chef and Daughter were so awesome and food was quick and delicious.  2nd visit - lunch - the Cuban was terrific!!! Got 1/2 dozen biscuits to enjoy over the holiday!  Only bad thing was all the styrofoam and plastic that came w out to-go order! Much better products out there that are less flimsy and better for the üåç
Love this place - huge and yummy biscuit sandwiches
Came here for a birthday brunch and fell in love.  We will definitely be back.  The food was amazing and coffee was superb.  Trust me and get the biscuit.
Sorry but the service and food is not great.
First experience today with a carry out sandwich for lunch. The chicken sandwich was amazing! Great fries, too. Nice staff. Thanks.
Hidden gem! The breakfast burrito is a must. Very welcoming environment with beyond friendly staff.

We had a party of 6 for breakfast at 10:30 am on Sunday, 11/6/22. Very chill vibes. We were in athletic clothes; others came in their church clothes. There was no wait for a table, but it did take a while for our food to come out. When we ordered, they said there were only 5 biscuits left, but they were open until 3:00, so I'm not sure why they wouldn't just make more. Luckily, we ordered in time to get the last biscuits.  Here's what I tried: - Veggie Omelet ($9.95): The omelet was really good! It came packed with veggies. I got it with a biscuit and home fries. The biscuit was buttered perfectly and was sooo delicious. The potatoes were seasoned really well and tasted great, but I wish they were crispy on the outside. - Regular Stack of Chocolate Chip Pancakes ($7.25 + $1.75 for chocolate chips): We got this to share between the 6 of us. They were fine, but I don't feel the need to get them again.  Toucan Louie's has good food at a reasonable price with large portions.

Go here!!! It is in an a bit of a sparse location, but is an easy drive from CLT airport. It completely exceeded our expectations. We got the chimichurri steak sandwich and a pimento bacon egg breakfast sandwich on a biscuit. Both were delicious. The cucumber salad was super fresh. And the coffee was good!
Amazing üëè
Eat here!

We ‚ô•Ô∏è this place! The food was epic, the vibes were excellent, and the staff was lovely. The coffee- oh my gosh! So delicious. Highly recommended for breakfast, brunch, and lunch! ‚òïüç≥ü•ûü•Øü•™‚òï

Accidentally stumbled upon Toucan Louie's today and so glad I did!!! The service was fast, friendly, and the food was delicious. I had the pimento, bacon and egg on a biscuit and OMG it was divine. Definitely recommend for a casual breakfast/lunch!

We had at a nice late lunch at this unassuming cafe on Rozzelle's Ferry. There's an "order here" sign at the register, but while we looked at the menus, the friendly cashier suggested we take them to a table and he'd come get our orders when we were ready.  We sat on the covered patio and enjoyed a breakfast burrito and jerk chicken salad sandwich.  Afterwards, craving something sweet, we went inside to look at their baked goods and decided on a blueberry biscuit.  All the food was good and really affordable at under $10.  You can conveniently pay on your phone too, at your own time when you're done.
Today was my first time eating from here and it was really good. I ordered a western omelet/ grits/ toast and EVERYTHING was good. I will return!!!
Nice southern breakfast food. Limited parking.
Waitress was wonderful!
Service was a little slow, arrived and was seated immediately. I ordered the scramble bowl and it arrived cold and the potatoes were undercooked. My waitress was friendly though.

I would not recommend Toucan Louie's because of how the staff treated us. We had a larger group come in. Our food was taking long time like 45 minutes to an hour to cook. When it came to our table it was cold and not all of us even got our food. It was taken back and the same food was brought back out to us. When we went to ask about it the staff proceeded to tell us that they touched our food and it was not cold. The fact that they said they touched the food then gave it back to us was not okay. Then they proceeded to throw our plates in our food away and cuss at us about the whole situation. It's not okay to do that to your customers. We did not yell or make a scene. We had a normal tone with them and they were very rude to us. I have never been to a restaurant where the staff threw the food away in front of us and to decided to cuss out the customer. I would not recommend this place to anyone because of the service we received.

We were 9 people, we literally waited for 1 hour, we got 5 plates and they were completely cold, others 4 never came out, the cooker was cussing us out and haven't even starter on the burgers. Never go there with a party.
Espresso was outstanding.
Make sure to try their homemade biscuits!
Best breakfast in Charlotte. Pro tip: buy a homemade Bo-berry Biscuit. The portions are always big and the service always comes with a smile, and a joke.
Love this place! Food is amazing, service is top notch, and the prices cant be beat. I love the atmosphere too. They teally support local businesses and have a lot of local ciders/beer/wine.
Great fresh-roasted coffee, excellent scratch-made food, and fantastic service! Highly recommend, this is going to be a regular stop when traveling to the airport!
They went out to their garden to pick fresh vegetables for our sandwiches, how fresh is that! Staff is friendly, food is delicious and tables are clean.
Chimichurri steak sub!!!!!! Fries is slaying!!!

Stopped by with a friend on our way through town when we needed a place to work with internet for awhile. Interior was clean and had a nice vibe, the food and drinks were great, and the woman working (shoutout Jaime!) was incredibly kind and attentive even though she was the only person working and was running the entire store alone.
I had the Cuban sandwich meal w/ FF and a sweet Tea. Sandwich had a heaping amount of meat and the flavor was outstanding ! Highly recommend this place for a bite to eat!
Super cute. Good fresh food. Friendly staff!
Great service and great food!!! Loved their Western omelette and home fries. Everything is made from scratch. Thanks to Cody for taking good care of my friend and I.
They market themselves as a roastery, but it's really more of a diner. The coffee okay diner coffee but nothing special.
My potatoes were over seasoned and not cooked all the way. Very unorganized
Outstanding! Best grits I've ever tasted, the Spanish omelet was perfection. My partner's biscuits and gravy were 6 stars. Excellent coffee, great service: a Charlotte gem, for sure!

If you want to spend 45 minutes waiting for a pancake this is your place. For such a small spot you'd expect basic breakfast items to come out a little quicker, place wasn't even full when we went on a Saturday morning.

Well I've given this place 3 tries. It's a cute place but unfortunately there's always an issue. I've always ordered to go and I'm always missing a part of my order. Last time the omelette was super salty. The second time I had ordered a fruit cup as a side and kid you not, it came in a dipping sauce cup- for $4 extra dollars lol. Today I ordered the pancake breakfast with blueberries and an omelette breakfast. I went in to pick it up and the older blonde lady behind the counter started yelling about how they didn't see the chow now order and didn't want to cook it. Then said ‚Äúyou're lucky I haven't tossed out the batter‚Äù, she was very rude. I think the guy at the register saw my face because he told me not to worry about paying for the coffee I had got while there. He was very sweet about it! When I got home I saw the pancakes had both blueberries and chocolate chips in it. All in all, better caf√©s to support in the area.

This place has an airy old charm atmosphere. We came for a late breakfast. I ordered the breakfast burrito which was tasty and large. I ate half and took the other half home to eat later. My wife and daughters split one large breakfast. Overall a good time was had by all. And, my eldest colored a beautiful picture of a whale.

I am confused about why we received our food after others ordered after us. The fruit was horrible. Some of the blueberries had mold on it. We had to ask for the coffee condiments. Had to ask for straws and then go retrieve them ourselves. Made to feel like we were not going to pay for the second cup of oj. I would not recommend this location to anyone who is traveling or used to top notch service.

Toucan louies is the place to go if you want fresh coffee (the owner roast his coffee beans himself), hot homemade food, everything is freshly made , to hand patted hamburgers, home made pancake batter , dressings, grits, Freshly squeezed lemonade ,etc. The atmosphere is extremely friendly and welcoming , there's even nice patio seating, they are also dog friendly!
Home made everything and you can tell Any other bad review is from Someone who hasn't stepped foot in a restaurant the restaurant Business

The woman working the coffee side was rude. She kept directing me away from her. She told me to have a seat, then took her sweet time, and then told someone else to finish. All the time she had no customers. The food is half decent. The shrimp and grits was like spaghetti. I would eat elsewhere.
This gem most definitely has a customer in me! Went in for the Sundays shrimp and grits, added bacon and it's amazing! This was my first and not last! Great portions and customer service!
Greek salad with shrimp excellent. Had enough for dinner too!
Superb staff,  magnificent menu, awesome atmosphere and fantastic food!
Great service,  cool people.  Best fresh food and coffee in the area hands down
Amazing breakfast!

Had a great breakfast at this very cute place. The food was prepared very well and the service was excellent. A local neighborhood place with not much fancy stuff, but that doesn't matter since the products and service were very well done. I will be back here often.

The staff here is amazing! The customer service is by far one of my favorite things about this spot aside from their great menu. I've come in unknowingly with 8 mins til closing and they were super polite even when I offered to leave they took my order made jokes and made me feel welcome. I would recommend this spot to any and everyone.   They are my favorite spot in west end!

3/10/2022. Decided to stop here for lunch.  A new spot to try!  I ordered the open face turkey sandwich with gravy which was delicious and reminded me of my moms version.  It came with mashed potatoes and green beans.  I saw on the counter a cake holder with turnovers in it and they looked homemade so I ordered the cherry one.  The food was good but the turnover was the star of the show!!!  I would recommend stopping here for lunch and definitely a turnover!
Good food. Will definitely go back
Great little place to eat, with interesting choices. Has a good drink selection. Very personable & friendly service. Definitely recommend.

Food and drink choices are great. Unfortunately I came for study time and the wifi is less than subpar. Couldn't load anything. Really a bummer because I enjoyed the place otherwise. Just don't come here planning to get anything done.

Our party needed a last minute place to get breakfast, and Toucan was able to accommodate and give us an amazing experience. They were incredibly kind and patient. The food was amazing and had the home cooked feel that you can barely find. The atmosphere was fun and everything was very clean. We will definitely eat there again the next time we visit  Charlotte

Overall I absolutely love this place! Everyone here has always been so friendly and so kind every time I come, and I literally come everyday lol mainly bc i just love the energy here good vibes!! Also the food is BOMB!

If I could leave nagative stars I would. I would rather dumpster dive than eat food from there again we ordered 3 omelets that were not cooked(goey) and obviously eggs poured out of a carton, they were all served with the worst cold home fries of my life , the bacon was disgusting with no flavor I really was astonished of how bad you could actually make breakfast food. The pancakes were like eating fluffy dry air , I would rather of eat a rice cake in syrup than these pancakes. We all threw out our food instantly after taking a bite of everything , the one thing I did eat however were the grits (decent) but made my stomach curl afterwards ...by far the worst experience for breakfast in my life or any food I ever ordered for that matter! If you want a horrible experience and to feel sock after then this is your place!
Good atmosphere & good food
Love this place, great food, great service and cool atmosphere.
Staff is sweet. Coffee was great.
Great food. Great service!
Lowkey, quirky spot.

Absolutely disgusting food!! I got a cuband drenched in grease, how do you mess up a cuban? My boyfriend got the turkey sandwich and the meat was such awful quality it was inedible!!! Not a hidden gem! Don't go!

Great little breakfast / brunch spot, if you don't mind home cooking and cheap mimosas. I took my girlfriend to brunch here and had a great time. We've been trying to support small local restaurants, and this is a good one. It's a bit off the beaten path, but is worth checking out. Friendly servers and great home cooked food. I recommend to anyone who wants a good breakfast or brunch. Also, very reasonably priced, considering the carafe of mimosa me and my girlfriend happily polished off. Not a conventional restaurant, more like a diner, but great if you want a fun eating experience.
Small cool little gem. Basic beer selection.. nice place to go to lay low and have a drink

Really solid diner in a part of charlotte about to explode with growth. I come here for lunch occasionally and am always satisfied by the food, service, and people. They've cultivated a pleasant, homey southern Cafe-diner experience. I do hope they get reusable utensils and plates soon, though.
Breakfast is good but lunch and dinner is very bad.
What happened to the ladies that used to make my breakfast burritos?? I hope they just had the day off because today I got pretty much an egg burrito....  üòû
Amazing breakfast burrito

Toucan Louie's is one of the best hidden gems in all of Charlotte. The food is delicious, the inside is low key and relaxed, and the staff is super friendly. If you haven't been yet, you're missing out. As a West Charlotte resident, this is definitely one of my favorites.

I didn't know this place existed. It's a chill place to hang out. Food was good! I had the Cuban Sandwich. I really like the Leg Lamp from The Christmas Story movie. Lady was nice so ill be going back.
Food was fine, but not good.  Bathrooms have many ceiling tiles removed. Tables sticky.

So I moved into a house three minutes from this restaurant and I had an awesome breakfast. I'm waiting on a stove so I'm having to eat out for another day or so. I went here for my dinner meal. The chicken wings were HORRIBLE and by the time I got home cold as was the mac and cheese. It's against health codes to serve this type of food especially the temperature of it. I will be reporting it and they were very much aware of what they served because I tried calling back twice and no one would answer. Not to mention I was the only customer who they were fixing food for. I have been in the business for thirty nine years and this by far is the worst food I have ever been served. You deserve 0 stars
Tastey cuban sandwich with cold beer
Very friendly staff and delicious sandwiches. Will come back soon!

Great spot for breakfast with really good coffee. The space is an old Esso station and we talked to owner Mark about how he transformed it into Toucan Louie's. Recommend the breakfast burrito and the pancakes. Mmmmm

Can I say YUMMY!!! This vegan was very happy with her lunch and my ladies at the clinic all had happy plates too! The hummus sandwich hit the spot. The ladies had the meal of the day, chicken pot pie and Classic tossed salad. Our new favorite spot! Thank you kindly!

First of all I want their buns but they're always sold out. I got buffalo wings which were crispy but a tad dry and the sauce was not buffalo-y. The mac&cheese was bland and not even a little cheesy. It was just yellow sauce not cheese.  The hospitality was phenomenal.
Awesome food and staff!
Quirky menu and *decor* with great food and service.
The food was pretty good. My first time eating there. Very friendly staff.
Great food, cool vibe, and service was good!
Good coffee, nice staff, chill atmosphere

Casual dining with an Island/Caribbean influence. A decent sized menu, enough to give variety but not so much it overwhelms you. My sandwich was bigger than I expected but you won't get any complaints from me! Try the hibiscus water, reminds me a lot of sorrel but lighter. Going back to try the cinnamon buns soon!
Good food and great customer service.
Very good Cuban bar b que sandwich

A unique little cafe/dinner with an old timey gas station theme/feel. Its a little off the beaten path, but worth checking out. I came for breakfast, and early in the morning it was just the owner running everything, and so the tables were a little dirty, but he was friendly and welcomed us in and brought menus to our table.  Side note, this is a police hangout. There were 2 cops waiting in the parking lot for it to open, and probably another 6 to 8 that stopped by while we were there. So don't speed anywhere near here, but it is definitely the safest cafe in Charlotte!  I had a coffee and the twisted goat breakfast sandwich. This place definitely isn't anything fancy, bit it's also not expensive. The coffee was no frills, bit definitely did the trick. The sandwich was a unique take on an egg and cheese, with peppers, mushrooms and feta that was reasonably good and well priced.  All in all not a bad spot for a breakfast meet up, won't knock your socks off, but probably won't disappoint either.

Love this little place! The owner is such a wholesome guy and the food and drinks are top notch! I have went so many times and have never been disappointed with anything I've tried though the Cuban sandwich, mac and cheese, and hibiscus water are my personal favorites.
$10 mimosa carafes for the win on Sunday. And the food was amazing
Simple breakfast experience with beer & wine bar inside. Mimosas are $2 on Sundays! Great spot for people watching.
Nice eclectic spot.. will be back
First time going and I had the steak sandwich and home fries.  They both were really good!!!  Place has a cool laid back vibe.  Staff were super friendly!!
Cool place. Staff was fun and kind, good beer selection and some unique food.
Good food friendly staff

The spinach salad with homemade blue cheese was absolutely amazing. I added the grilled shrimp to it that was saut√©ed to perfection. The staff was so kind, and friendly. I will definitely be back to try more of there menu options. Also I will try to add photos next time (it was so good I was only thinking about eating it)

What a great brunch spot! The biscuits and gravy were divine. Mimosas by the carafe and an on-site pop up sticky bun shop make it over the top. Its counter service so it gets full fast but our party of 5 got a table with no wait!!
Was not the best eggs were very dry
Cute restaurant to hangout and enjoy a nice burger !
Amazing food and super nice staff!

This cozy little restaurant was a pleasant surprise after we traveled around the outer city rim of Charlotte. They have great staff, decor, and the food is amazing for such an affordable price. They have local beers, board games, and host a trivia night as well. Certainly worth checking out if you are a local or out of town and want to try some new.
Good coffee and sandwiches from folks who take building community seriously.
Went for breakfast..food & the food prices were great! The service was outstanding.  Glad we stopped by.
Very much enjoyed the chicken pot pie special for lunch!

This place is a is a hidden gem!!! It has a homey vibe to it. The people are nice and very friendly. The food is good and very fair priced. They have a variety of unique beers and homemade food and coffee. Don't judge this book by its cover!!! Stop in for a bite and your will definitely be back for more
Maria was wonderful! Very friendly and eager to recommend places to visit around town. Food was delicious, portions were bigger, and priced very fairly. 100% coming back if I'm in Charlotte again.
Hands down the best biscuits that i have had.
Been going to this place for the last month excellent service great atmosphere and classic old timey restaurant. Not to mention, excellent sausage gravy biscuits the size of my hand.
Very nice clean and comfortable place invited guests come in for a while it's nice love the ambiance people are very cordial and nice

I love it here! They have breakfast lunch and dinner, very cute place super friendly and they have new Cinnamon bun vendors üòç ü§§ whenever I'm out and I need brunch or lunch I'll always stop by! They make amazing smoothies too!

Found this on our way to the Sistine Chapel exhibition.  Wonderful food and quick! I had Turkey, hummus, w. Goat cheese sandwich and Hubby had a burger.  Definitely would go back if we were in Charlotte again.
(Translated by Google) Good food, very kind and friendly personalized attention!  (Original) Buena comida, atenci√≥n personalizada muy amable y amigable!
great food

My wife and I stumbled across this place on our drive back to Philadelphia from Charlotte. The staff was very friendly, service was very good and the food was even better. I'd recommend this place if you're passing through or even if you're a local.
loved it food cheap n freash
Good food, but not very clean.

Outdoorsy, pickneck tables below. Nice brewery albert small was clean. No food on-site. Bartender was great in recommending beers. Black Blaze milk stout was awesome if you like dark beers. Better than Guinness. Nitro infused on pouring gives great taste.
Cool little place.
Great food, staff was great.  Order came out quick and was delicious!  And the ice is great... No lie.
Service was fantastic and the food was delicious
Great atmosphere owner is very friendly and has a variety of foods and beverages
I enjoyed myself here. Nice, clean. Service was great, food was wonderful
This place is good, you should go. Good Sunday morning breakfast spot.
Wow! Excellent everything - food, coffee, service, ambiance.
Very nice place and friendly staff. We had breakfast there today and it was delicious!
Great new place. Cooked my turkey bacon good and crispy. Most places burn it when I ask for crispy. Great service!! They have a variety of Kambucha. Excited to try espresso drink next time!
Love their turkey club!!!
Loe this place, a great little neighborhood spot.
Amazing
Cozy atmosphere with delicious food!
Their drinks are popular in our house, specifically their chai tea latte and iced coffee.
This place was a hidden gem ! Service was amazing.  Good was amazing.  And the design is super cute and welcoming.  Will defenitly be back
I favorite spot to eat at on Sunday's ü§≠‚ù§ü§™ü•∞

I ordered inside and it took  7 minutes.... Build your own 4 pack of beer. Mostly ipa. Cucumber salad tastes like healthy bread and butter pickles. My BBQ Cuban sandwich was literally falling apart when I bit into it. Lots of soggy bread. Tasted great but I wish my bun was toasted more...I don't even think it was toasted At all....I also expected it to be a hot sandwich.
Fantastic and breakfast ALL Day!! Cool place and nice vibe.
Great food as always.

This is a hidden gem in Charlotte! I'm visiting from CT and was looking for a Sunday brunch place. All the ‚Äútrendy‚Äù overpriced places had at least an hour wait. When I called to see if they had availability, they said to come right down. We got here to a converted gas station that had kitschy decor. If there's not one but TWO Fra-GEE-Lay lamps from ‚ÄúA Christmas Story,‚Äù you know it's gonna be a cute place.  The food was delicious, healthy, INEXPENSIVE,  and the customer service was great that I came back a second day in a row before I traveled back home.  I also liked the fact that they used paper plates and plastic utensils in these Covid days.  The hipsters should really come here instead.
Chunks of flour batter in a cooked pancake?
BLT was fantastic
Nice location
a little gem in the west end. i order the salad's and they are lovely and fresh. we order takeout and packaging is sustainable and eco friendly. super reasonable prices

Absolutely wonderful experience. We stopped in late. Food was delicious and at a great price. The owner brought treats and water for our dog and lit the fire pit outside just for us. Totally above and beyond. Hoping to move to the area but would make the drive regardless.
Usually come in ONLY during breakfast hours. Today I took a chance and had the lunch special. Salmon Cakes, Cucumber salad, & beans. Great spot!!
Delicious food, quick service, no glitches with on line ordering, it was great!

My husband and I were in Charlotte on a weekend vacation. We found this little spot from a google search. We were impressed instantly and actually went back twice over the weekend. The food was delicious and the staff went above and beyond for us. We look forward to going back on our next getaway!
Consistently great food and the people here always go out of their way to make sure everyone has a good experience.
Good cubans

First time today trying this place and i must say it satisfied my taste buds....never had a breakfast biscuit like they make theirs...but ohhh my it was good.... Can't wait to try some of their lunch options and oh yea had a macchiato to go with my breakfast plate and it was good as well!!!!
I had an amazing visit here, great food! great for hanging with friends.
Very friendly, great service, great food. Good pricing. Something for everyone's taste!

Worth the drive...no matter where you are!  I found Toucan Louie's by mistake, or rather, out of desperation.   It is an oasis in this otherwise sparse neighborhood.  TL is like Rhino Market ‚Äî only better.  Way better. It's cleaner, cuter, and the food is crazy good.  The turkey sandwich sets a new standard for Turkey Sandwiches: with hummus, roasted peppers, goat cheese, olives, spinach, cucumbers.... a magic flavor I cannot forget.  Owner Mark looks like an unlikely chef, but brims with passion for the food ‚Äî and drink ‚Äî that he crafts on-site, including the local ingredients he sources from his farmer friends.  All that plus craft beers and wine to accompany his all-day breakfast, lunch and more menu.  Thanks Toucan Louie's!   See you soon!
Toucan Louie's is a diamond I'm the rough! The service was excellent and the breakfast foods we tried were delicious. The coffees and teas were also great! We will definitely be back.
Cool eclectic spot.
No problem no arguing no fighting all was well

My first experience was delightful, so much so I'd put these guys in a category that I haven't been able to find: Healthy, tasty and reasonably priced (below $10) meals.  I went for Meatloaf Monday and let me tell you, I'll be back for more. If my mom could make a meatloaf this mean, I'd be like Will Ferrell, yelling for Ma to bring it down.  I'll be checking out their other daily specials, maybe even bring a date one day if I'm feeling frisky, they've got a cool ambiance and some good beers on tap.
Awesome place, owner marc hooked me up with a soft drink I've been trying to find locally.
Love to support local but sadly the shrimp & grits were so greasy we couldn't eat them. The grits were floating in a bowl of grease.
I felt sick after eating here. Maybe it was an off day. My friends didn't feel too great either. None of us finished our food. Not impressed. Won't be back.

A hidden little gem. We found this as it was the only coffee place open in the afternoon. The owner is wonderful and the food was amazing! I recommend the twisted goat breakfast sandwich, a good vegetarian option available all day
The pancakes here were delicious! The biscuits and gravy was another amazing dish! Definitely recommend breakfast here!

First of all; the menu is great! I wanted to order everything!!!! Lol... The customer service and teamwork is "hi five"! To have breakfast served all day, and still have other great lunch/dinner options will keep you coming daily! My food was cooked well and to my liking!!!!! I've already shared links to view your website to a few people; but 1 thing is for sure, I'll be back for more!!!!!!!!! Keep up the gr8ness!
Nice and healthy
Best grits in town
BLT, yummy every time!

Toucan Louie's is one of our favorite spots. It has great food, and is locally owned. We love mondays because kids eat for $1.50. Our kids love to go play games. They just got some beers on tap as well so we will be going to check that out sometime soon!
Good food, good prices, quick and convenient!!

Good. Bigger sandwiches. Really like the cucumber salad side, could eat it every day. Almost like a bread and butter pickle, the red onions aren't overbearing, and it's all still pretty crunchy. VERY satisfying side.
Great food. Quick and polite service. Awesome beer on tap

Food was mediocre. Had the pimento cheese Philly. Meat was dry and the pimento spread was bland. When I went in for pickup there were two people inside eating. One person working the kitchen and he wasn't wearing a mask until he saw that I had one on.
This is a very quaint place. The food was helluva good. We had the breakfast burrito and 2 eggs, grits, bacon and biscuit. I also ordered a Turkey Club. They were spot on. We will definitely return.
Great personalities and sandwhiches

Great local spot with lots of local favorites. Beer, kombucha, wine and lots more. Jerk chicken salad is awesome and the wings are delicious. The prices are great as well. I highly recommend this place

We enjoyed brunch here after they opened from the COVID shutdowns. What a great experience! Food was amazing. Staff was so friendly and even though we were the only ones in the dining room and it appeared that they must be used to having a packed-out house, we felt so comfortable and enjoyed every bit of that experience. I don't know how they operate when they are slammed with people and I hurt for businesses that don't have the normal amount of guests at this time but this is one place I'll visit again if I'm in the area.

I started going here when I moved to Charlotte towards the end of last year. compared to Charlotte the prices are really cheap for some of the things such as their  combos (not so much single items like certain sandwiches). You can get eggs pancakes toast and a side of something like grits for $6. But for some reason they also charge the same price for a lot of their single sandwiches (weird).  The food is good but on my last visit I got a biscuit and pancakes and was very disappointed. The pancake was just really dry and not very tasty as if they used no butter. And the biscuit they make now is apparently pan baked as if  they are trying to save money and is the worst tasting "biscuit" (if you can call it that) I've ever had. It's literally just bread that has absolutely no flavor. I would use store-bought white bread for biscuits and gravy before I got theirs again. This sadly is a deal-breaker for me. Outside of these two things I would definitely recommend the place.
Favorite place to stop for breakfast!
Their Cuban sandwich and wings are gooood!! üëçüëç
Great atmosphere and food.
Awesome place for coffe and casual meetings
Love this place!!!!  Perfect little spot to grab great food , beer, coffee and cool other stuff.  Great service as well!

What a wonderful place. This is our second visit and we will be back again. The menu is great and has you covered from breakfast, to lunch, dinner, and late night snack. The staff is friendly and responsive.  We've enjoyed the Cuban, Chimichurri steak, and turkey feta and spinach wrap. All the dishes we've had have been just wonderful.  If you have an opportunity to meet the wonderful owner Mark, ask him or the staff about where they got their name from it's a great story.  In addition to the great menu they also have a nice selection of items that you can carry to go including things like wine, craft beer, specialty nonalcoholic beverages. They also have the most amazing black garlic. If you've never had it it's a must try and worth the visit itself.

We're making our way through the the Yelp top 100 list and this was our most recent stop.  It's a cute little no frills market over on the west side. The parking lot is small, but we came for lunch on a weekday and it wasn't crowded so we got a spot.  The ordering process was a bit awkward. The person taking our order seemed confused, but it all worked out.  We got the Chimichurri Steak and Cuban BBQ sandwiches with a side of mac and cheese, a lemonade, and a slice of apple pecan cake.  The Cuban BBQ was my favorite. The meat was perfect and I loved the slaw. The Chimichurri Steak Sandwich was good, but I didn't taste any chimichurri sauce which was disappointing. The cake was fantastic.  The only let down was the mac and cheese. It tasted like Velveeta cheese and just wasn't very good. I wouldn't get that again.  After we sat down and got our food someone came and made sure we had everything we needed. They also do free refills on their homemade lemonade which is really nice.  If you want a good sandwich and a relaxing place to hang out, this is your place.

My first reviews of Toucan Louie's were positive, like other reviewers I drive by this everyday leaving work.  So when some of us from work decided to try it, the food was expensive but not terrible.  Mind you even my co-workers would tell you while I am not a penny pincher, I do not want to be over charged.  One of my co-workers and I went today because it is close, we had not been much since the price increase maybe 8 months back, so I think this was the third time in 8 months this is a change from 2-3 times per month. I ordered a peanut butter and bananna sandwich (includes a honey drizzle and seed) and an order of mac and cheese along with a fountain Diet Coke, the Diet Coke is almost always flat.  The price was $11.05, this is a ridiculous price and we will very likely not be back till someone can expense this on a business account.  Don't get me wrong I prefer to support small business and I have had conversation with the owners, but for lunch this is just to much money.  I think it is funny, with a lower price (but still to high) I was willing to go 2-4 times a month, with the price increase I may go every 10-12 weeks.  I figure when I was going more often he made more money off me, may have been smaller bites of money but would you raither make $4.00 profit per meal 3 times a month or $6.00 profit per meal 1 time every 2-3 months.  Now it is not just me, I have several people that I take to lunch with me on a daily basis, so now it is not that I do not go but at least three (sometimes more) do not go through the doorway, meaning even more money lost.  Today the owner came in because of kitchen printer issue, he seems to have problems with it and proceeds to throw some items in the back, this was very unprofessional, and it looked like it even scared/startled the cook.  I like the owners and wish them well, but the food is just too expensive for what you get in return.  I am sure I will be back but likely this is down to 1 to 2 times per year now. Scott W.

We both had the pancake platter. It was delicious. I did try the apple pecan cake- DELISH! Better than these bakeries I've been to. Def going back. My toast was not even toasted. I threw the majority of it away.  I had very high hopes for this small business but was let down.

My first experience was a decent one, and I was surprisingly impressed. Well, this is my second go-around, and I came with my Mom, who is a cook and does breakfast for over 100 customers almost each day. This experience was awful. Eggs were burnt, the ham was comped together like it was initially frozen like that. The pancakes were under cooked. My Mom wasn't impressed. The excuse was that the griddle was too hot. There is no excuse for brunt eggs. Still, service was friendly, and they replaced the eggs. However, they were still burnt but now not cooked. We just threw out the food and went somewhere else. So this place is not consistent so go on your own risk.

This is a quaint neat restaurant. And I do enjoy visiting but it just seems the amount of food you get is shrinking in quantity based on going when they first opened. When we first started going the food was more plentiful, now that they have a following it seems the quantity of provided food has dwindled. Today my peanut butter and banana sandwich only had a small amount of peanut butter. Also my mac and cheese side was just over half full. When we were first going there the side was packed whether you got beans, home fries (packed in), mac and cheese was a full cup, however the last couple times it has been very near half to just over half full. Mac and cheese, home fries, beans are all very inexpensive to serve, and I expect a plentiful amount.  The parking is here is terrible, you can't really fault the restaurant for this as they are making use of all available space but most frequently we have to park down the street or across the street.  While I do recommend the restaurant, and the food is good.  There value is not really there.  Will I continue to go? Sure, but just not more than once a month or so.

Locally sourced and reasonably priced in a clean, fun atmosphere. This new place has quickly become a family favorite. I also really appreciate that I can eat there and not worry about how my food was treated before it came to the restaurant since they use small, local farms to supply them.  The owner told me she toured a large, brand name poultry farm and couldn't stay more than 10 minutes- didn't even finish the tour. She said she grew up on a farm and couldn't stand the way they were doing things and how the animals were treated.  I appreciate that.  The food is REAAAAAALLLLY good, too. If you care about and love tea and coffee this is a place doing it very well. They roast their own and the tea guy is really into his craft.  I can't recommend this place more.
